The paper deals with algorithms for combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms are based on analyzing the opportunity costs of accepting certain bids, which involves analyzing the structure of the bid graph (cs.DS). The algorithms are designed to maximize revenue, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation ratios and running times, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.LG, cs.DM).
